export const PATRICK_DOCS = "# Anthropic\n\nTo use **Claude** models, add an\n[Anthropic API key](https://console.anthropic.com/) in your profile.\n\n```text\nProfile → AI → Provider: Anthropic → paste your key\n```\n\nClaude models are a strong default for drafting and reviewing claim amendments\nand office-action responses.\n\n---\n\n# Install\n\nPatrick is currently an **unsigned Windows desktop app** (the alpha).\n\n<Callout type=\"note\" title=\"Windows only, for now\">\nThe alpha ships as a Windows installer. macOS and code signing come with the beta.\n</Callout>\n\n<Steps>\n\n<Step title=\"Download the installer\">\nGrab the latest installer from the [releases page](https://github.com/mhurhangee/patrick/releases/latest).\n</Step>\n\n<Step title=\"Run it (past SmartScreen)\">\nOn first launch, Windows SmartScreen may warn \"Windows protected your PC\" — click **More info → Run anyway**.\n</Step>\n\n<Step title=\"Add your AI key\">\nPatrick uses **your** provider key. In the app, open a profile and paste it:\n\n<Tabs>\n<Tab label=\"Anthropic\">\nGet a key from the [Anthropic console](https://console.anthropic.com/), then **Profile → AI → Anthropic → paste your key**.\n</Tab>\n<Tab label=\"OpenAI\">\nGet a key from the [OpenAI platform](https://platform.openai.com/), then **Profile → AI → OpenAI → paste your key**.\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n</Step>\n\n</Steps>\n\n<Callout type=\"tip\">\nYour key stays on your machine and talks only to the provider you choose — you pay them directly, usually pennies per response.\n</Callout>\n\n## Next steps\n\n<CardGrid>\n\t<Card title=\"Set up your profile\" href=\"/docs/concepts/profiles\">\n\t\tYour identity, AI settings, and how Patrick writes.\n\t</Card>\n\t<Card title=\"Open your first task\" href=\"/docs/concepts/tasks\">\n\t\tPoint Patrick at a folder you already have.\n\t</Card>\n</CardGrid>\n\n---\n\n# Welcome to Patrick\n\nPatrick is an **agent-first patent-prosecution assistant**. It drafts and redlines\noffice actions and claim amendments directly in your own Word files — as native\ntracked changes you approve — and runs entirely on your own computer.\n\n## Open · Transparent · Yours\n\n- **Open** — Apache-2.0, and your work lives as plain `.docx` / `.pdf` in your own\n  folders. No proprietary database, no lock-in.\n- **Transparent** — you see exactly what the agent is told and doing: the system\n  prompt, its reasoning, every tool call, and the running cost.\n- **Yours** — everything stays on your machine, including your AI keys. There is\n  no Patrick server.\n\n## How it works\n\nYou point Patrick at a folder you already have (a matter), and it reads the\ndocuments inside. Ask it to draft a response or amend a claim, and it proposes\n**tracked changes** in a real Word file — accept or reject each one, just like a\ncolleague's redlines.\n\n[Install Patrick →](/docs/getting-started/install)\n\n---\n\n# OpenAI\n\nTo use **GPT** models, add an\n[OpenAI API key](https://platform.openai.com/) in your profile.\n\n```text\nProfile → AI → Provider: OpenAI → paste your key\n```\n\n---\n\n# Profiles\n\nA **profile** is you — your identity, your AI provider and keys, and the **prompt**\nthat steers how Patrick works. You can keep several (for example a shared \"client\nprofile\" preloaded with that client's style and examples, for consistency).\n\n## What's in a profile\n\n- **Identity** — your name, firm, and **practice context** (a standing description\n  of how you work).\n- **AI** — your provider (Anthropic / OpenAI / Google), key, models, and reasoning\n  effort.\n- **Prompt** — the template that instructs Patrick, with tokens like `<TASK>` and\n  `<PRACTICECONTEXT>` filled in automatically.\n- **Examples** — writing samples so Patrick matches your voice.\n\n## Let Patrick help\n\nThe practice context and the prompt are the blank-page parts. Open a task, then\nask Patrick in the chat — it can **draft your practice context or improve your\nprompt**, proposed as an accept/reject card.\n\n---\n\n# Tasks\n\nA **task** is a folder you already have, opened in Patrick. Your source documents\nare never modified — Patrick reads them and proposes edits in separate, editable\ncopies you own.\n\n## The brief\n\nEach task has a short **brief** — a one-paragraph statement of the objective. It\nframes everything Patrick does. Right after opening a folder, ask Patrick to\n**draft the brief from the documents**.\n\n## Notes\n\nA running **notes** record (decisions, findings, strategy) lives in the sidebar —\nyou and Patrick both add to it as the matter progresses.\n\n## Your files stay yours\n\nPatrick never renames, moves, or deletes your originals. Drafts it creates are\nclearly marked and live alongside them in the same folder, as plain `.docx`.\n\n---\n\n# Patrick, the agent\n\nPatrick is one agent that works **inside your documents** through tools — it reads\nthe live document, finds text, and proposes **native Word tracked changes**.\n\n## Human in the loop\n\nPatrick **proposes**; you decide. Edits arrive as tracked changes you accept or\nreject. Bigger moves — opening a document, creating a draft, saving a note — come\nas **accept/reject cards**. Nothing happens behind your back.\n\n## Transparent by default\n\nFor every turn you can see:\n\n- the **system prompt** it was given (yours to read and edit),\n- its **reasoning** and every **tool call**,\n- the **tokens and cost**.\n\n## One Patrick\n\nThere's one Patrick per chat, with one set of instructions frozen for that\nconversation. Start a new chat to change the instructions.";
